Microsoft buys jClarity to boost Java on Azure 

With its acquisition of Java support services company jClarity, Microsoft is making a play to optimize Java workloads on its Azure cloud platform and increase the Java community engagement.

 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 

There Is Always More to Learn

 
 
 
 
 

The JPMS Maturity Model

The JPMS Maturity Model described in this post is a very interesting proposal for classifying interoperability of tools, libraries and frameworks with JPMS. This model gives users a clear indication of how well their tools of choice support the module system and informs maintainers which features they could target next.

 
 
 
 
 
 

Who Needs Lombok Anyhow

Java is quite a verbose language and annotations can solve almost any problem. Right? - What a dangerous combination that is. Yet another interesting opinion on how Lomboks magic might be harmful if you do not know what goes behind the scenes.

 
 
 
 
 
 
 

Containerizing Apps with jlink

In this article, you will see how to use jlink, which is a command-line utility available since Java 9, to create easy-to-containerize Java executables. These executables are with a trimmed-down version of the JDK and in this era of containerization, that means small Docker images.

 
 
 
 
 
 
 

Testing Microservices: an Overview of 12 Useful Techniques - Part 1

The combination of a microservice architectural style and container-based infrastructure requires a testing strategy that is compatible with this brave new world.
In this article you will explore 12 common techniques used when testing microservices.

 
 
 
 
 

Moving From Reactive Programming To Reactive Architecture: An Overview 

The missing bridge link between Reactive Programming and Reactive Architecture. See how you can apply Reactive Programming for Microservices integrations with this first article of the series.

 
 
 
 
 

Enum Mappings with Hibernate The Complete Guide 

Most developers use enums in their domain models as they provide a strongly typed way to model an attribute that has one out of a list of defined values. 
With JPA and Hibernate, you can map enums in different ways. Lets take a look at the different options.

Feature Toggles for Spring Boot applications with Togglz 

Togglz is a very nice library that helps you apply feature toggles (feature flags) without the need to redeploying your application and the great news is that it is very easy to setup and comes with a good Spring Boot integration. 

 
 
 
 
 
 

Multiple Cache Configurations with
Caffeine and Spring Boot

In many applications including plain Spring and Spring Boot, you can use @Cacheable on any method and its result will be cached so that the next time the method is invoked, the cached result is returned.
However, when it comes to configuration @Cacheable is somewhat inflexible. See how you can overcome this problem by setting up a cache that will work with multiple cache configurations for expiry time, initial capacity, max size etc.

 
 
 
 
 

Chronicle Map Series

In this great series of articles you will learn how you can utilise the Chronicle Map library to create a GC-friendly, distributed key-value store with additional persistence.
Part 1, Go Off-Heap
 Part 2, Super RAM Maps
 Part 3, Fast Microservices

 
 
 
 
 

MicroProfile Platform

What exactly is the MicroProfile release? It combines specifications which the community considers necessary for developing microservices with Enterprise Java. In this RefCard you will see how these specifications provide an alternative to Spring with the intention to provide lightweight and developer-friendly APIs.

 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 

REST-Assured With Cucumber: Using BDD for Web Services Automation

While many teams use Cucumber to describe their UI testing, this open source software can be used for web service scenarios as well. See how you can easily integrate it with a really cool Java testing framework that has done all of the heavy lifting: Rest-Assured.
